<TITLE> Hockey players skip training in protest </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 30 (bdnews24.com)  The national hockey players skipped a training session on Monday to demand the announcement of the inter-club players' transfer as well as increase facilities for the national team. The players also complained that federation officials had yet to fulfill the promises made in early February. The hockey players of the SA Games camp had earlier boycotted the camp for three days in protest at sub-standard food and poor accommodation facilities. They eventually returned to training after being assured by Bangladesh Hockey Federation president Khandokar Jamiluddin. The players said on Monday that they were yet to given a proposed reception from the federation for their triumphant Asia Cup qualifying campaign in Singapore. The players, however, said that they would return on Tuesday under the supervision of new German coach Gerhard Peter Rach, who arrived in Dhaka two days ago. bd
